{% if task_provider == 'microsoft-todo' -%}
## Microsoft To-Do

Microsoft To-Do syncs via the Graph API using device-code flow authentication.
No app registration required — the script uses Microsoft's public CLI client ID.

### 1. Test authentication

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/tasks-import/import_tasks.py --test-auth
```

On first run this opens a browser sign-in prompt (device code flow). Follow the
instructions in the terminal. After authenticating, the token is cached in the
macOS Keychain and an auth record is saved to `data/ms_auth_record.json` for
silent re-authentication on future runs.

### 2. First sync

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/tasks-import/import_tasks.py
```

### 3. Inspect

```bash
sqlite3 data/tasks.db
> SELECT title, status, due_date FROM tasks WHERE provider='microsoft-todo' ORDER BY due_date;
```

### Troubleshooting

- **Token expired / auth failure**: delete `data/ms_auth_record.json` and
  re-run `--test-auth` to re-authenticate.
- **Azure CLI alternative**: if you prefer `az login` over device-code flow,
  you can register your own app and set `AZURE_CLIENT_ID` / `AZURE_TENANT_ID`
  in `.env`.

{% elif task_provider == 'todoist' -%}
## Todoist

### 1. Get your API token

1. Go to https://todoist.com/app/settings/integrations/developer
2. Copy the **API token** (40-character hex string)

### 2. Add to .env

```bash
echo "TODOIST_API_TOKEN=your_token_here" >> .env
```

### 3. Sync

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/tasks-import/import_tasks.py
```

This pulls all active tasks and the last 200 completed tasks. Todoist rate-limits aren't hit at this scale — safe to run frequently.

### 4. Inspect

```bash
sqlite3 data/tasks.db
> SELECT title, status, due_date FROM tasks WHERE status='open' ORDER BY due_date;
```

{% elif task_provider == 'things' -%}
## Things 3

Things 3 stores its data in a local SQLite database. No auth needed — just Full Disk Access for macOS.

### 1. Grant Full Disk Access

System Settings → Privacy & Security → Full Disk Access → add Terminal.app (or your shell).

### 2. Sync

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/tasks-import/import_tasks.py
```

The script auto-discovers the Things database at:
```
~/Library/Group Containers/JLMPQHK86H.com.culturedcode.ThingsMac/ThingsData-*/Things Database.thingsdatabase/main.sqlite
```

### 3. Inspect

```bash
sqlite3 data/tasks.db
> SELECT title, status, completed_at FROM tasks WHERE provider='things' LIMIT 20;
```

### Notes

- Things 3 is macOS/iOS only
- The skill reads the Mac database; iOS/iPadOS tasks sync to the Mac via Things Cloud
- Read-only — this skill never modifies the Things database
{%- endif %}

## Not Just Task Management

Remember: this skill is for **cross-source coherence**, not task management. Use it to answer questions like:

- "Did I create tasks for the intentions I wrote about last week?"
- "Which tasks have been open longest?"
- "Am I completing tasks in line with the goals in my notes?"

Use your actual task manager for actually managing tasks.
